UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Notes:: AS: NS (Strong Maybe) Spiky: 0.5 (Tech spike) EF/FF: FF Founder Archetype: 7 FMF: 8 Thesis: 7 + Strong pedigreed team with domain experience. + Already have ongoing paid pilots with Airbus, Safran, Ministry of Heavy Industries. ? Yash is scientist archetype, not articulate but possesses clear tech spike. ? How big of a market is this? Path to $100 M ARR is unclear. Meeting Notes Team - Abhishek Chopra (CEO and Co-Founder) - Rut Lineswala (Co-founder) - Team size: ~40 people Problem - Current simulation software extremely slow & computationally expensive - Engineers forced to choose between: - Example: Aircraft simulations take 6 months on 250,000 parallel computers - Algorithms haven’t changed since 1970s - GPUs underutilized (only 30-35% capability used in engine simulations) Product - BQFi: Backend engine for simulation software - Uses quantum-inspired algorithms on existing hardware - Key features: - Technical differentiator: Uses stochastic math & quantum-inspired gates - Can find global minima faster than genetic algorithms Go-to-market - Initial focus: Aerospace & Defense sector - GTM Strategy: Conference presentations, keynotes, booth setups - Position as backend engine for existing simulation software - Target customers: Airbus, Israel Aerospace, Air Force Research Lab - Future expansion planned into biotech, pharma, finance Traction - Major pilot with Airbus: - Pipeline includes: Funding - Currently raising seed round: - Series A metrics set:' WHERE id = 68 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
