UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Ref from Anand (CEO @ MinIO): Got a ref from Anand, CEO @ MinIO; Great kid and sharp, but concerns on 0-1 and will leave this in the pass category for us. - Top 3 engineers for his tenure that AB has seen over the years - Problem solver and will be able to figure out any domain you through at him - Steep learnings curve - Humble, seeks advice, etc - H&H - worked amongst the hardest in his team ? Needs direction for 0-1. someone has to guide him the right direction. Can solve problems, but needs a guiding hand on what problem to focus on; ? Not angel investing because of the domain. AB doesnt get the space and not sure why sid picked it. Detailed notes Anand context - deeply involved in product and engineering side - he was part of our AI team - he was under 2 other AI leads - He started as an intern - he was a fresher but worked at a senior engineer levl - he was part of senior discussions as well - very good problem sovler - he is the perfect kid every parents dreams of - very skilled, hardowrking, no bad habits, sharp - He works really hard; hardest in the team - Skillset wise - fast learner - very sharp learning curve - how you think about rpoblem solving and picking the right approach, he had good clarity - what i dont know enough - his domain in real estate - picked real estate as a market but i cant guage enough on wether its a real problem - realtors are bad customers - dont know how big it is - Relative grading to others - dont like interns - but he was one of the few...' WHERE id = 92 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Ashwin''s Series A Notes - Summary - 2026-01-30: **Founders:** Akash, Neel, Prajwal - All IITM ''22 grads, no prior work experience. **Round:** Series A - $10M raise, wants $80M post. Has offer from US fund at lower valuation. **KP Views:** WMB and pass - also speaking to seed investor for reference. **NOTE FOR V:** FYI in case you''d like to meet them, but Ashwin doesn''t see us doing this round. --- **POSITIVES** **Tech spike:** Strong technical team solving tough challenges. **Founder quality:** "Akash is sharp and spiky on intrinsics. Not overly aggressive, but he''s consistently been at it." **Traction (~$2M ARR):** Added ~$1M ARR in last 6 months. --- **CONCERNS** **Thesis - AI-first Loom:** Shoot explainer/product videos with AI voiceovers, graphics, auto-zoom. "Started with L&D, then moved to sales, then customer success, and now thinking of jumping to marketing. Overall, the approach feels too iterative for my liking - throwing 10 things at a wall to see what sticks." **GTM:** "Growth is good, but there''s still no repeatable GTM motion. It feels sporadic and heavily LinkedIn-driven (founder posts)." **ACVs:** Mostly less than $5K. Largest enterprise customer ~$40K, but most are small teams. **Auto content updating:** Looking to launch feature connecting to video repositories. "Companies like GitHub have dedicated teams for this, so it could be an interesting thesis. But given how much they''ve jumped around historically, I''m not confident this will stick either."' WHERE id = 94 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Marketscan & Breakdown by Trinika 2025-09-12: Hi Team, Adding the breakdown of market landscape and workflow in the excel here Quick summary of key questions below: ![](cid:3199483326*image001.png@01DC22BC.55A4C510) Is the problem big enough? - Yes, because in a content/video production process, three prep tasks - proxy creation, renaming/restructuring, and audio–video sync - together take ~5-7% of the total production budget and ~10-15% of assistant editor time. - Example: a 60-second ad or micro-drama with 4 cameras and separate sound typically needs 20-30hrs from AE before the first cut - iteration speed is higher for microdrama so faster speed req - TAM (for these three steps): Global ~$3B; US ~$1.2B. - SAM (automation wedge): Global ~$1.5B; US ~$0.5B. - At 10% penetration of SAM: ~$150M ARR global; ~$50M ARR US Big gaps in workflow today? - Camera card to storage: For most cameras, copying from card to local drive and cloud is still manual. Only Canon paired with Frame.io (Adobe-owned) auto-copies to both. - Transfer & naming: Cameras save files as C0001 or A002C012; editors need script-friendly names like Scene3_Take5. Renaming remains manual. - Project & bins: Folders nomenclature varies from agencies to agencies – some do it by - day, by actor, or scene. No tool auto-restructures into clean bins/folder by scene/shot/take. - Audio–video sync: Tools handle clear lip-sync, but struggle when lips aren’t visible or timing is creative. Example: a voice-over on a montage, or...' WHERE id = 95 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'AI notes: This transcript captures a reference check call with Rohit about Vishal, a former colleague from LiveSpace, followed by a discussion about Aptile''s upcoming product launch. Reference Check on Vishal Background and Role at LiveSpace - Vishal was among the first four team members at LiveSpace - Worked at LiveSpace for 5-6 years (2015-2021) - Grew from software engineer to director of engineering - Headed the CMS and pricing engine for on-demand construction of home interiors - Managed complex technical systems independently without much support Working Style and Strengths - Described as reliable, dependable, and level-headed - Technically outstanding and thoughtful in decision-making - Calm demeanor, especially during conflicts or heated discussions - More prepared and thoughtful before communicating ideas - Works well with different personalities in cross-functional settings - Considered among the top 5 team members Rohit has worked with Areas for Development - Not naturally charismatic or outspoken in communication - Might face challenges in business model development and identifying margin opportunities - As a technical founder, may need complementary skills for business aspects - Would benefit from hiring team members with complementary business skills Aptile Product Launch Discussion Action Items - [ ] Rohit to prepare and send early access package including: - [ ] Rahul and Mohit to help promote Aptile on LinkedIn (they have 110K and 50-55K followers respectivel...' WHERE id = 96 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
