UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Prep 2026-03-19T23:33:00.000+05:30: Confluence Labs (YC W26) | confluence.sh What they do AI research lab building foundation models optimised for learning efficiency in data-sparse domains — drug design, materials science, hardware engineering, physics discovery. Their thesis: modern ML only excels where you can collect massive training data. In domains where data is expensive or slow to generate (physical experiments), current AI fails. Confluence''s approach: combine LLMs with discrete program synthesis to maximise what you can learn from a small number of experiments. Two-track strategy: 1. Hypothesis generation — AI that designs maximally informative experiments so each one teaches you the most 1. Data-efficient modelling — program synthesis + LLMs to make predictions with far fewer data points Technical milestone Came out of stealth with 97.9% on ARC-AGI-2 at $11.77/task — SOTA at launch (Feb 2026). ARC-AGI-2 is considered one of the hardest AI benchmarks in the world (tests novel reasoning from just a few examples). Approaching 100% on what was previously considered unsolvable. Open-sourced the solver. Backed by YC and Paul Graham personally. --- Founders 1. Brent Burdick (Co-Founder) — [LinkedIn not publicly indexed] 1. Niranjan Baskaran (Co-Founder) — linkedin.com/in/niranjan-baskaran-a906a5205 Both are extremely young (combined age ~43), no traditional industry pedigree — pure research talent profile. The Paul Graham backing is notable signal here.' WHERE id = 103 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
